Ferocity <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukreelosthehunter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kreelos the Hunter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 173<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/8/02 3:48:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1162.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_devil.gif" align=absmiddle>  Ring of The Light Policy</span><hr size=1> We have a policy in The Ring of The Light.  It states that we shouldn't give gear to people they could not reasonably expect to have 20 seasons beyond their current experience.  It's a subjective policy, impossible to enforce, but it gives us a general guideline we use between twinking and helping. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ularalyfv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Laraly FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/8/02 11:37:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1162.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_devil.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Twinks</span><hr size=1> Don't forget about the bazaar, it makes it possible for low levels to find gear that probably isn't something they could get at their level. Polished Steel Ulaks for example, they're a dime a dozen, sell very cheap, but they are a nice weapon for a young monk and not something a newbie could ever hunt for.<br>
<br>
Also makes it possible for them to make alot more money at the newbie levels than before the bazaar. Start in QH and collect snake eggs the first three levels, stacks of those sell well, hit WK and you have pelts and spider silk to sell, again very good money. The bazaar makes it possible to sell this stuff for decent money very fast. By the time you need a magic weapon to hunt wisps and really make good money, it's quite easy to be able to buy one in the bazaar. <br>
<br>
Does this make them twinks? I don't think so, they worked for the items they sold in order to be able to afford a piece of nice gear, just like we do at later levels. Anyway, just pointing out that while yes, a level 1 with a Waki is most assuredly a twink, though I don't care if he is, alot of these newbies are working hard and taking advantage of the new game mechanics to have pretty good gear.<br>
<br>
